title: Eddie_Cochran_4CD
description:
Eddie Cochran influenced everyone from
The Beatles who saw him play in the early
1960's in England to Marc Bolan of T. Rex
to Punk Rockers that admired his three 
chord style. He was a combination of a
few old things and a few new things, 
he was a Rocker and a Crooner, and
a Gentleman. Eddie, like Buddy Holly,
is someone that will live forever, as
long as there are kids with a new guitar
that learn their first three chords.
